    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-09-12T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-09-12T03:00:00-05:00" n="193"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d193">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/23</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GJW2"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gerard</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="italic">Berlin</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-09-12T09:00:00+01:00">
                        <hi rend="italic">September 12, 1914, 9 a.m.</hi>
                    </date>
                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 10:30 p.m.</hi>] </dateline>
                <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                <p>110. I presented the matter referred to in the conversation between Mr.
                        <persName>Oscar Straus</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_BCJHV1">Count
                        Bernstorff</persName> in an informal manner not wishing to receive a refusal
                    so formal as to prevent future similar offers. Have had no answer but know that
                    time is not yet ripe. I think possibly the Kaiser’s letter to the President
                    about dumdum bullets, etc.<note n="1" xml:id="d193fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_794">p. 794</ref>.</note>,
                    offers an opportunity to get in the situation in a conciliatory capacity and
                    suggest that you request me to investigate the charges made.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GJW2">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Gerard</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
